  "A GPS system calculates an aircraft's bearing using theta = arcsin(d/R), where d is horizontal distance and R = 6371 km (Earth's radius). If the aircraft moves so that d changes at 800 km/h, how fast is theta changing when d = 3185.5 km (approximately R/2)?": "",
